OL,6,FInstead ministers hope to secure a
OL,7,Fprivate partner to open up co-
OL,8,Finvestment options but see urgent
OL,9,Ftemporary action as necessary to keep
OL,10,Fthe plant running. However, it's
OL,11,Funderstood that a later change in
OL,12,Fownership would be a likely future
OL,13,Foutcome.
OL,15,FIn response to questions about whether
OL,16,Fgovernment control would extend to
OL,17,Fnationalisation, the prime minister
OL,18,Fsaid MPs would be "passing legislation
OL,19,Fto take control of the plant and to
OL,20,Fpreserve all viable options".
